    {
      "id": "happy",
      "levels": [
        {
          "front": "happy",
          "back": "행복한",
          "romanized": "haengbokhan",
          "grammarNote": "'행복하다' (haengbokhada) = to be happy (deep, lasting happiness). '기쁘다' (gippeuda) = to be glad/delighted (in the moment). Korean emotions are adjectives that become predicates: '행복해요' (haengbokhaeyo, I'm happy), '기뻐요' (gippeoyo, I'm glad)."
        },
        {
          "front": "I'm very happy today.",
          "back": "오늘 너무 행복해요.",
          "romanized": "oneul neomu haengbokhaeyo",
